romote a coherent sense of "Soviet" identity during the interwar years. This book investigates this failure to mobilize society along communist lines by probing the secrets of the party's ideological establishment and indoctrinational system. An exposé of systemic failure within Stalin's ideological establishment, Propaganda State in Crisis ultimately rewrites the history of Soviet indoctrination and mass mobilization between 1927 and 1941.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aIdeologyxHistoryxSoviet Union. 0aIdeologyzSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aIdeologyzSoviet Union. 0aPolitical culturexHistoryxSoviet Union. 0aPolitical culturezSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aPolitical culturezSoviet Union. 0aPopular culturexHistoryxSoviet Union. 0aPopular culturezSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aPopular culturezSoviet Union. 0aPropaganda, SovietxHistory. 0aPropaganda, Soviet. 0aPublic opinionxHistoryxSoviet Union. 0aPublic opinionzSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aPublic opinionzSoviet Union. 0aState-sponsored terrorismxHistoryxSoviet Union. 0aState-sponsored terrorismzSoviet UnionxHistory. 0aState-sponsored terrorismzSoviet Union. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 20th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300159639423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300159639.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles